The paper deals with issues related to reinforcement learning, specifically in the context of Markov Decision Processes (MDPs). The paper discusses concepts such as value functions, policies, and regret, which are central to the field of machine learning. The paper also provides experimental results to support the theoretical analysis. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
